# HTML Code Copy Buttons

When creating or updating HTML documentation that contains code snippets, add a copy button in the upper-right corner of each code block.

Requirements:

- Wrap code snippets in a relatively positioned container, for example `<div class="code-block">`.
- Place a visible copy button at the upper-right corner of the container.
- Add JavaScript that copies the text content of the corresponding `pre code` block to the clipboard.
- The button should give short feedback after copying, such as changing text from `复制` to `已复制`.
- Keep the feature self-contained in the HTML file with inline CSS and JavaScript unless the project already has a shared HTML asset pattern.

Example structure:

```html
<div class="code-block">
  <button class="copy-button" type="button">复制</button>
  <pre><code>example command</code></pre>
</div>
```
